"{\"uid\": \"skift.com-2024-07-09-boeings-guilty-plea-airbnbs-olympics-pitch-and-questioning-carbon-offsets\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Photo Credit: Flags promoting the Paris 2024 olympics hang from a lamppost in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 84, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 78, \"end\": 83, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997216946, \"rank\": 2.781933651464833e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Skift  Today's podcast looks at Boeing's guilty plea, Airbnb's Olympics tourism angle, and the trouble with carbon offsets.\", \"from\": 86, \"to\": 209, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 140, \"end\": 146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Airbnb\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Select a question above orask something else  Good morning from Skift.\", \"from\": 211, \"to\": 281, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 275, \"end\": 280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skift\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Skift\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skift\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skift\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's Tuesday, July 9, and here's what you need to know about the business of travel today.\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 372, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Apple Podcasts|Spotify|Overcast|Google Podcasts  Boeing will accept a guilty plea dealfrom the Department of Justice over charges the planemaker misled federal authorities on certain aspects of the 737 Max 8, which has been involved in fatal crashes.\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 624, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Airlines Reporter Meghna Maharishi lists three takeaways from Boeing's deal with the Justice Department.\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 729, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 643, \"end\": 649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meghna_Gulzar\", \"score\": 0.9864535224328803, \"rank\": 0.013732503784984718, \"text\": \"Meghna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meghna_Gulzar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meghna_Gulzar\"}, {\"begin\": 650, \"end\": 659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maharishi\", \"score\": 0.9813110412008954, \"rank\": 0.019044887924893533, \"text\": \"Maharishi\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maharishi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maharishi\"}, {\"begin\": 710, \"end\": 728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Department_of_Justice\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6250140455597214e-14, \"text\": \"Justice Department\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Department_of_Justice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Department_of_Justice\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boeing will have to pay a more than $240 million criminal offense fine and invest at least $455 million in compliance and safety programs.\", \"from\": 731, \"to\": 869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The planemaker will be on probation for three years, during which it would need to install an independent monitor to oversee its compliance and safety.\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 1021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, Boeing would not have any protection from any ongoing or future federal investigations.\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Next,Airbnb has unveiled a new adurging travelers heading to Paris for the Olympics to avoid hotels to discover the true essence of the French capital, reports Executive Editor Dennis Schaal.\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1130, \"end\": 1136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Airbnb\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\"}, {\"begin\": 1186, \"end\": 1191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997216946, \"rank\": 2.781933651464833e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1261, \"end\": 1267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.7360610521983647, \"rank\": 0.35671081523187953, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Airbnb's ad features a family of four dealing with common tourist come-ons outside of a hotel before the hotel collapses.\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1439, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1318, \"end\": 1324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Airbnb\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The hotel gives way to an Airbnb, and afterwards, the family views an artist painting on a canvas and a couple dining, among other sights.\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1466, \"end\": 1472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Airbnb\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The narrator then urges travelers to stay where the locals live instead of the touristy part of the city.\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1684, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, the effectiveness of carbon offsets has been a contentious issue in the travel industry.\", \"from\": 1686, \"to\": 1783, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Research Analyst Robin Gilbert-Jonesexplores the reasons carbon offsets are controversialand how they can be effectively evaluated.\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1915, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Travel brands are increasingly turning to carbon offsets - considered a way for companies to compensate for their own emissions by reducing them elsewhere - to help reduce the industry's massive carbon footprint.\", \"from\": 1917, \"to\": 2129, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Gilbert-Jones notes the carbon offset market has been described as the \\\"wild west.\\\"\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And one carbon credit may look like another but be much less effective at reducing CO2, which leads companies to seek out the cheapest credits available.\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2376, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gilbert-Jones listed five recognized ways to measure the quality of a carbon offset, including verifiability.\", \"from\": 2378, \"to\": 2487, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Verifiability means a legitimate third party can verify claims of carbon avoidance in offset projects.\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2590, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Producer/Presenter: Jose Marmolejos  Skift's in-depth reporting on climate issues is made possible through the financial support of Intrepid Travel.\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2612, \"end\": 2627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jos\\u00e9_Marmolejos\", \"score\": 0.999997523808698, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jose Marmolejos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jos\\u00e9_Marmolejos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jos\\u00e9_Marmolejos\"}, {\"begin\": 2629, \"end\": 2634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skift\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Skift\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skift\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skift\"}, {\"begin\": 2724, \"end\": 2739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intrepid_Travel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Intrepid Travel\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intrepid_Travel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intrepid_Travel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This backing allows Skift to bring you high-quality journalism on one of the most important topics facing our planet today.\", \"from\": 2741, \"to\": 2864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2761, \"end\": 2766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skift\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Skift\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skift\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skift\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Intrepid is not involved in any decisions made by Skift's editorial team.\", \"from\": 2865, \"to\": 2938, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2865, \"end\": 2873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dodge_Intrepid\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9204313987109859e-16, \"text\": \"Intrepid\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dodge_Intrepid\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dodge_Intrepid\"}, {\"begin\": 2915, \"end\": 2920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skift\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Skift\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skift\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skift\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Curated byDarin Graham  Climate Reporter  GreenShifttakes a deep dive into the intersection of climate change and the travel industry.\", \"from\": 2940, \"to\": 3074, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get it in your inbox the first of every month  By submitting this form, you agree to receive email communication from Skift.\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3200, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3194, \"end\": 3199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skift\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Skift\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skift\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skift\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tags:airbnb,boeing,climate change,paris,skift daily briefing,skift podcast  Boeing has accepted a guilty plea deal with the Department of Justice over misleading authorities about the 737 Max 8, resulting in a $240 million fine and a three-year probation with compliance monitoring.\", \"from\": 3202, \"to\": 3484, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3214, \"end\": 3220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing\", \"score\": 0.9999992131677939, \"rank\": 7.868328901797021e-07, \"text\": \"boeing\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boeing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Airbnb launched an ad for the Paris Olympics urging travelers to stay in local neighborhoods instead of hotels to experience the real Paris.\", \"from\": 3485, \"to\": 3625, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3619, \"end\": 3624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997216946, \"rank\": 2.781933651464833e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The travel industry is scrutinizing the effectiveness of carbon offsets, with Robin Gilbert-Jones highlighting five measures to ensure their quality, including verifiability.\", \"from\": 3626, \"to\": 3800, \"entities\": []}]}"